(251, 1, '2015-03-05 05:36:18', '2015-03-05 05:36:18', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]<strong><em>Most professional wedding photographers in Sydney charge $2000 - $12000 per wedding. What are you getting for your money?</em></strong>\n<ol>\n	<li>Time - The average wedding will take me 60 hours from start to finish. As a professional photographer that specialises in attention to detail I will spend a lot more time in editing to get a product that I am happy with. So where is the 60 hours?</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n	<li>Meeting the couple - I need to understand your family dynamics to ensure all the moments that are important to you are captured. Getting to know you as a couple is extremely important as it will allow me to work comfortably around you, your family and your friends on your special day. Nobody should be on a blind date with their photographer on their wedding day.</li>\n	<li>Equipment preparation - a few days before the wedding all equipment will be checked and packed. As a minimum this is what equipment I carry:\n<ul>\n	<li>Nikon D4S</li>\n	<li>Nikon D3S</li>\n	<li>Nikon D800</li>\n	<li>Sony a7S</li>\n	<li>Nikon 14-24mm f2.8</li>\n	<li>Nikon 24-70mm f2.8</li>\n	<li>Nikon 70-200 f2.8</li>\n	<li>Nikon 85mm f1.4</li>\n	<li>Nikon 105mm Macro f2.8</li>\n	<li>Sony Zeiss 55mm f1.8</li>\n	<li>Nikon SB 910 x 2</li>\n	<li>Nikon SB 700</li>\n	<li>Selection of Lensbaby lenses</li>\n	<li>Selection of light modifiers</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n	<li>The big day - this will start with the groom and bride getting ready and may finish as late as the bride and groom departing the reception. During this time I will generally shoot about 3000 photographs. My aim is to capture the rare and spontaneous moments for you and your family. The time allocated to the formal wedding photographs may vary from 30mins - 2 hours.</li>\n	<li>Editing and processing - ever tried to sort through 3000 photographs? It takes time. After sorting images, they then are colour and tone corrected. Where required further enhancements are added to give that magic touch.</li>\n	<li>Artwork creation time - this is where I complete your wedding album or slideshow. Images are also prepared for you to share easily on social media. Any prints that you have requested undergo special colour checking and calibration with the printer and paper that is being used. This ensures that the images that you see on my computer match the photographs that I deliver to you.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n	<li>Time to meet again - now you get to finally see some of your photographs and make a decision on the final product.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n<ol start="2">\n	<li>Cost of goods - Wedding albums are expensive to create - both from a time perspective and also from a cost of manufacture. Wholesale cost of wedding albums to the photographer usually range from $500 - $3000 and a top of the line wedding album can cost in excess of $5000. Those prices do not include the time that I have spent editing the photos and the considerable time that goes into the design of the wedding album design.</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n<ol start="3">\n	<li>Cost of equipment - Professional camera equipment is expensive. My current equipment retails at more than $60,000.</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n4. Cost of running a business - Most reception venues in Australia require a photographer to be insured for 20 million dollars of liability insurance. Then there is the extra cost of insuring the camera equipment. Advertising, accounting, marketing, and general business expenses all add to the cost of running a business.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Ever Wondered Why It Costs So Much To Hire A Wedding Photographer?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '248-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-03-05 05:36:18', '2015-03-05 05:36:18', '', 248, 'http://localhost/samantha-ohlsen-photography/248-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
